text.section:
Unless otherwise exempted by KRS Chapters 600 to 645, the juvenile session of the District Court of each county or the family division of the Circuit Court shall have exclusive jurisdiction in proceedings concerning any child living or found within the county who has not reached his or her eighteenth birthday and who allegedly:
Is beyond the control of the school or beyond the control of parents as defined in KRS 600.020;
Is an habitual truant from school;
Is an habitual runaway from his or her parent or other person exercising custodial control or supervision of the child;
Is dependent, neglected, or abused;
Has committed an alcohol offense in violation of KRS 244.085;
Has committed a tobacco offense as provided in KRS 438.305 to 438.340; or
Is mentally ill.
